<font color="#FF0000">THE BASE</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 26 21:53:59 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I lived on Walter Reed for 9 years of my childhood while the war was &quot;deescalating&quot;. My father was a doc serving at the base, and did so for almost twenty years. I have not been back there for some time now, but reading the postings stirs up many visions of the past; legless men, sad faces, scruffy beards, all seen throught the eyes of a child who could not comprehend what it was all about. I guess some things never change because I am still sad and confused just as I was then. I hope they are all well.
<p><code>-- tdhl@montana.com  (Dan Landes) </code><p>


